args:
When the prince tries to convince Ed to stay
behind, Ed tells them how he was abandoned.
Finally, the prince decides to let Ed help search
for his missing brother, but as they near the
building, the environment of the lake takes a
turn and they are attacked by dragons anew!
Over there! Thank Ilia the child\nappears to be all right.
It is too dangerous to go alone.\nCan you not simply return home\nand wait for us to finish this task?
My home is where my brother resides.
Look, I understand that your brother\nis important to you. I really do. Butâ€”
My father abandoned me\nwhen I was a child.
But my brother said he needed me.\nThat is why I must go to him.
I see. That sounds very difficult.
What would you think if our situations\nwere reversed, {player_name}?
If someone said you were not needed and\ncast you aside. What would you think?
I suppose I've never really thought\nabout that before...
But if someone did tell me that, I suppose\nI'd look for some way to be useful so I\ncould show this person they were wrong.
The blood of the Alberian royal family\nruns in my veins, after all.
And that means it's my duty to serve the\npeople, no matter what form that takes.
And what if you were not royalty?

Yes, say you were one of the smallfolk.
A base person of no real consequence.
And then, one day, people decided you
were not needed. What would you think?
Honestly? I don't know. I suppose\nI would feel untethered, in a sense.\nLike I was sort of...losing myself?
Anyway, that's enough of this talk, Ed.\nWe'll go look for your brother together.
I want to reunite Ed with his brother,\nand that's where we're headed. Plus...
Well, I think I understand his feelings.\nI know what it's like to care for your\nsiblings. I know how hard it can be.
*sigh* Yer as soft a touch as ever.\nFine, then. Let's do this thing.
He would not be the prince we all know\nand love if he did any different.
Yeah, siblings are important and all that.\nGood. Fine. But you still gotta stick close\nso ya don't get dead, okay, Ed?
And with that, let's be off!
Well, we're a lot closer to that building,\nbuuuut ummm...
Great disgusting pondwater!\nCheck out the lake!
It is foul in both odor and appearance.\nCould its mana have been corrupted?
The forest creatures seem antsy, too.\nIt's like they're all scared of something.
I sense no water dragon here.
A lake of this size should have a dragon\nto safeguard its mana, yet I detect only\na wet and barren waste.
Whatever's going on here, I bet it has\nsomething to do with that facility.
Two of 'em! Dammit all to hell,\nI think we just walked into a trap.
If Phares is trying to stop us,\nhe's going to be very disappointed.
Let's defeat these dragons\nand keep Ed safe!
